Slight Webb Data inspection¶

Date: 26Jan2024¶

Author: Jrose¶

Here I am loading in an anndata object I created from the downloaded seurat object from the Slight-Webb study.

This study included scRNA + CITEseq of 29 individuals (SLE and HC) of either white or black ancestry

I'm not sure what cell types are included so hoping to find out here.

In [1]:
import scanpy as sc
import os

data_dir="../data/SlightWebb"
file="SlightWebb_AnnData.h5ad"

adata_path = os.path.join(data_dir, file)

adata = sc.read(adata_path)

Exploration¶

Now let's do a little exploring to see what sort of gene expression these B cells have without having to recalculate much in terms of variable genes, umap, pca, etc
